---
import Layout from "../../../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="IELTS Writing Lessons — IELTS Corner"
  description="IELTS Writing lessons: Band 7+ structure, coherence, task response, and precision."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="hero" style={`--hero-bg: url('/heroes/lesson.png');`}>
      <div class="hero-content">
        <span class="pill">✍️ IELTS Writing</span>
        <h1>Band 7+ is structure + precision. Not fancy vocabulary.</h1>

        <p class="muted" style="max-width: 60ch;">
          Writing scores drop for predictable reasons: unclear position, weak paragraph logic, and grammar
          mistakes that signal low control. Fix the system, and your score follows.
        </p>

        <div class="cluster">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/essay-correction">Essay correction →</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/lessons/ielts">Back to IELTS lessons →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="height: var(--s-8);"></div>

    <div class="grid grid-2">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>What you’ll train here</h3>
        <p class="muted">
          Task 2 argument structure, paragraph unity, linking without over-linking, and sentence control
          (accuracy + range).
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>What the examiner really wants</h3>
        <p class="muted">
          A clear answer to the question, developed ideas, and language that stays correct under pressure.
          Simple + correct beats complex + broken.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="height: var(--s-7);"></div>

    <div class="surface feature">
      <div class="feature-grid">
        <div class="stack">
          <h2>Band 7+ backbone (Task 2)</h2>
          <p class="muted" style="max-width: 62ch;">
            Use this spine: <strong>Position</strong> (1 sentence) → <strong>Roadmap</strong> (1 sentence) →
            <strong>Body 1</strong> (idea + explanation + example) → <strong>Body 2</strong> →
            <strong>Conclusion</strong> (restate, don’t add new ideas).
          </p>

          <div class="cluster">
            <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/essay-correction">Get feedback →</a>
            <a class="btn" href="/tutoring">Coaching →</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-2" style="gap: var(--s-4);">
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Introduction</h3>
            <p class="muted">Paraphrase + position + 2-point roadmap. No history lesson.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h3>Body paragraph</h3>
            <p class="muted">One main idea only. Explain it, then prove it with a specific example.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h3>Coherence</h3>
            <p class="muted">Logical flow beats “more linking words.” Use linking to show meaning.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h3>Sentence control</h3>
            <p class="muted">Mix simple + complex safely. Avoid risky structures you can’t control.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="height: var(--s-8);"></div>

    <h2>Quick writing drills</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-2">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Thesis + roadmap drill (3 minutes)</h3>
        <p class="muted">
          Write 2 sentences only: your position + your 2 main points. Do this daily with new prompts.
          This builds clarity fast.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Paragraph unity drill</h3>
        <p class="muted">
          Write one topic sentence, then three supporting sentences that all match it.
          If one sentence doesn’t support the topic sentence, delete it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="height: var(--s-8);"></div>

    <div class="grid grid-2">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Need marking + corrections?</h3>
        <p class="muted">If you don’t get detailed feedback, you repeat the same mistakes forever.</p>
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/essay-correction">Essay correction →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Back to IELTS lessons</h3>
        <p class="muted">Go pick another skill and keep the system consistent.</p>
        <a class="btn" href="/lessons/ielts">Go back →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
